  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                  Plot Outline
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
        
   First there was the gold rush, over 100 years ago, when tens of thousands
   of prospectors with dollar signs in their eyes headed into northern Canada 
   to seek their fortunes. Today it is the diamond rush which is attracting 
   miners. Beneath the barren wastelands of Canada's Arctic tundra there are 
   millions of dollars worth of diamonds. And the new prospectors are digging
   in.
